The paper presents a novel approach to learn a kernel-based regression function using a stochastic convex optimization procedure. This falls under the category of machine learning and optimization, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as it covers the core topics of the paper. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as it covers topics related to learning and optimization. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is another possible category as kernel-based methods are commonly used in computer vision tasks. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are less likely but still possible categories as they cover topics related to optimization and learning.
